714548f-a.title: Manhattan: 78th Street (East) - Lexington Avenue
714548f-a.text:
East 78th Street. north side, east from Lexington Avenue.
Note the row of grivate residences bearing No's. 153 to 163
(Shown in View 2). That, ad foining the apartrent house
(No. 169 E. 7Rth Street) and bearing awnings ia referred
to in an article by Lee. E. Cooper in the N.Y.Times of April 26,
1939. Mrs. Anna Drewnick in 1929 combined these buildings into
a single spacious dwelling with a carden at the rear, at a cost
of 4175,O00. A deal recently consummated by Warren L. Marks,
Daniel Brener Inc. will result in frther changes by an undisclosed
purchaser. This sale was subject to a 1ease expiring Sept.39,
1939 and held by the tenent, Alfred H. Schoellkopf, president of
the Niagara Hudson Power Corp.
